69
00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:03.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not once did he consider
making her a vampire

70
00:05:03.094 --> 00:05:05.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and bringing her into our community.

71
00:05:06.973 --> 00:05:11.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are loyal to Dracula
and the night world, aren't you?

72
00:05:12.520 --> 00:05:14.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You would have protected her.

73
00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:17.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course I would have.

74
00:05:19.986 --> 00:05:21.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Carmilla] Of course you would.

75
00:05:25.283 --> 00:05:26.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Carmilla] But, on some level,

76
00:05:28.119 --> 00:05:32.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he considers us less important
than the brief life of a mistreated pet.

77
00:05:34.625 --> 00:05:36.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Does that sound sane to you?

78
00:05:39.630 --> 00:05:41.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It sounds...

79
00:05:43.176 --> 00:05:44.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
confused.

80
00:05:46.888 --> 00:05:49.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And now he has taken us to war.

81
00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:54.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Should this war be prosecuted
by a confused man?

82
00:05:55.813 --> 00:05:57.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I-I don't know.

83
00:05:59.650 --> 00:06:05.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
