will leave the castle to take the town.

112
00:07:49.886 --> 00:07:54.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My own forces will take the castle
and unseat Dracula.

113
00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:56.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Saving your life.

114
00:07:57.935 --> 00:08:01.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Going forward to control
and surround the human race.

115
00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:07.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

116
00:08:08.362 --> 00:08:10.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dracula is powerful.

117
00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:14.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your forces alone may not be enough.

118
00:08:16.537 --> 00:08:17.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're right.

119
00:08:18.706 --> 00:08:22.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Brilliant Hector. They may not be.

120
00:08:23.961 --> 00:08:26.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which is why you must do something for me.

121
00:08:32.053 --> 00:08:33.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

122
00:08:36.557 --> 00:08:39.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[howls]

123
00:08:49.111 --> 00:08:51.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

124
00:09:01.165 --> 00:09:03.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Isaac]
I heard you moving across the sand.

125
00:09:06.629 --> 00:09:08.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's very good, Isaac.

126
00:09:09.298 --> 00:09:11.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Most people can't hear me moving at all.

127
00:09:12.677 --> 00:09:15.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's nothing out here but the sand.

128
00:09:16.097 --> 00:09:19.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And even the wolves
don't come close to my little home.

129
00:09:20.643 --> 00:09:24.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What brings you out here?
-You.

130
00:09:25.064 --> 00:09:27.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have need of my work.

131
00:09:28.025 --> 00:09:30.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Invite me across your threshold, Isaac.

132
00:09:36.325 --> 00:09:39.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Dracula]
Do you remember how we first met, Isaac?

133
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:41.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Isaac] That would be difficult to forget.

134
00:09:42.707 --> 00:09:44.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[liquid pouring]

135
00:09:44.500 --> 00:09:48.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
