for one final time,

149
00:10:36.552 --> 00:10:38.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they must be punished.

150
00:10:40.014 --> 00:10:41.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
War, then?

151
00:10:42.308 --> 00:10:44.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You need an army of the night?

152
00:10:44.977 --> 00:10:48.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You sound suspicious.
-You're not human.

153
00:10:48.898 --> 00:10:50.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your passions are rare and pure.

154
00:10:51.484 --> 00:10:53.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"War" sounds like a small thing, for you.

155
00:10:54.987 --> 00:10:58.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's the word you choose,
but it's not what you mean.

156
00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:03.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. I mean to end the human race.

157
00:11:04.914 --> 00:11:07.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-And you want my help to do it.
-Yes.

158
00:11:09.126 --> 00:11:12.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Even though I'm a human being.
-Yes.

159
00:11:14.256 --> 00:11:16.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you remember my first words to you?

160
00:11:18.219 --> 00:11:19.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

161
00:11:20.096 --> 00:11:22.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Indulge me, Master Dracula.

162
00:11:23.099 --> 00:11:25.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So that I may know
you are still my friend.

163
00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:27.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You said,

164
00:11:28.354 --> 00:11:33.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"I have no fear of death.
It always sounded peaceful to me."

165
00:11:35.694 --> 00:11:37.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will be loyal to the end.

166
00:11:38.322 --> 00:11:39.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And beyond.

167
00:11:40.658 --> 00:11:41.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let us begin.

168
00:11:53.754 --> 00:11:56.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[neighs]

169
00:11:56.799 --> 00:11:58.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[high-pitched neigh]

170
00:12:03.389 --> 00:12:06.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Drinking fucking pig blood? Fuck no!

171
00:12:07.351 --> 00:12:11.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are the generals of the court
of Vlad Dracula Tepes,

172
00:12:11.772 --> 00:12:14.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and we deserve a proper fucking drink!

173
00:12:15.901 --> 00:12:19.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The maps say there's a town
20 miles away from here.

174
00:12:21.240 --> 00:12:23.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They will never see us coming,
and fuck them if they do.

175
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:26.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tonight, we feed.

176
00:12:27.621 --> 00:12:28.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[horse neighs]

177
00:13:00.946 --> 00:13:01.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[exhales]

178
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:34.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[hammer clanging]

179
00:14:04.009 --> 00:14:04.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isaac.

180
00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:09.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I feel like the tone of the war hall
is turning against me.

181
00:14:10.224 --> 00:14:12.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Even Hector looks at me
as if he no longer knows me.

182
00:14:13.978 --> 00:14:18.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have respect for Hector.
But he is a gentle soul.

183
00:14:18.732 --> 00:14:19.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's still a little boy.

184
00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:23.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Probably the same little boy
who didn't understand

185
00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:27.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-why he was beaten for keeping pets.
-[chuckles]

186
00:14:28.409 --> 00:14:33.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, his pets <i>were</i> reanimated
dead animals.

187
00:14:33.789 --> 00:14:37.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One can understand
any parent's discomfort

188
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:40.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with a dead cat doing a dance
in the living room.

189
00:14:42.006 --> 00:14:44.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Isaac] He really only wants pets,
you see?

190
00:14:46.176 --> 00:14:50.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He really only understands pets.
That's how he perceives your war.

191
00:14:51.974 --> 00:14:57.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To cull humans back to a small population
and then keep them in pens,

192
00:14:57.605 --> 00:14:58.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he understands that.

193
00:14:59.857 --> 00:15:01.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is partly my fault.

194
00:15:02.651 --> 00:15:07.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's a child in a man's body.
That does make him easy to lie to.

195
00:15:08.574 --> 00:15:12.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are Dracula.
No one has a right to your true beliefs.

196
00:15:14.038 --> 00:15:16.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Not even you?
-Not even me.

197
00:15:18.542 --> 00:15:21.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've given me purpose
and treated me with respect.

198
00:15:22.671 --> 00:15:24.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A lie wouldn't change that.

199
00:15:25.674 --> 00:15:29.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are unique.
You don't owe anybody anything.

200
00:15:31.221 --> 00:15:34.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You, Isaac, are the only one
I've told the truth to.

201
00:15:35.392 --> 00:15:40.397 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because I believe you are the only one
who grasps the necessity of it all.

202
00:15:43.776 --> 00:15:46.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You rarely come to my working place.

203
00:15:47.237 --> 00:15:50.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How can I be of service to you,
Master Dracula?

204
00:15:53.744 --> 00:15:55.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you still my friend?

205
00:15:57.247 --> 00:15:58.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Always.

206
00:15:59.708 --> 00:16:01.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then know that you may be alone.

207
00:16:12.179 --> 00:16:14.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[wind howling]

208
00:16:24.274 --> 00:16:26.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[horses neighing]

209
00:16:31.573 --> 00:16:32.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

210
00:16:38.747 --> 00:16:40.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

211
00:16:49.425 --> 00:16:51.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

212
00:16:53.804 --> 00:16:55.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[squelching]

213
00:17:02.479 --> 00:17:04.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[groaning]
-[grunting]

214
00:17:18.203 --> 00:17:19.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman screaming]

215
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:35.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[snarls]

216
00:17:59.161 --> 00:17:59.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you okay?

217
00:18:01.705 --> 00:18:02.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tired.

218
00:18:04.958 --> 00:18:05.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sleep, then.

219
00:18:07.669 --> 00:18:09.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A bit lonely.

220
00:18:14.718 --> 00:18:16.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My dusty old sheet is big enough for two.

221
00:18:18.055 --> 00:18:20.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And nobody was ever lonely in this house.

222
00:18:26.605 --> 00:18:27.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

223
00:18:28.857 --> 00:18:29.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is Alucard asleep?

224
00:18:31.777 --> 00:18:34.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He says he's slept enough.

225
00:18:34.113 --> 00:18:38.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's still poking around your family's
things with a look of faint disgust.

226
00:18:38.242 --> 00:18:39.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Heh.

227
00:18:39.535 --> 00:18:41.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's lonely even when you're standing
next to him.

228
00:18:42.621 --> 00:18:43.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's strange.

229
00:18:44.581 --> 00:18:45.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How so?

230
00:18:46.458 --> 00:18:47.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure.

231
00:18:48.669 --> 00:18:52.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's intelligent, sometimes even witty,
in his way.

232
00:18:53.549 --> 00:18:55.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And he's certainly half-human.

233
00:18:55.843 --> 00:18:58.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
More than half-human.
He's a person in his own right.

234
00:19:00.681 --> 00:19:03.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it's like he's a cold spot
in the room.

235
00:19:05.310 --> 00:19:08.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It's not like your sadness.
-I'm not sad.

236
00:19:09.356 --> 00:19:10.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, you are.

237
00:19:11.108 --> 00:19:13.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I can shout at you, or tease you,

238
00:19:13.193 --> 00:19:16.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and get a reaction
that lets me know you're still in there.

239
00:19:17.656 --> 00:19:21.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His sadness is like an icy well.
It's bottomless...

240
00:19:22.327 --> 00:19:25.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and it swallows up your voice
and anything you try to drop into it.

241
00:19:26.331 --> 00:19:28.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Am I really sad?
-All the time.

242
00:19:29.918 --> 00:19:32.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't even notice it now.
It's just how you are.

243
00:19:34.631 --> 00:19:36.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And then, sometimes...

244
00:19:37.384 --> 00:19:39.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you'll tell me nobody's ever lonely
in your house,

245
00:19:40.512 --> 00:19:43.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-and offer me your stinky blanket.
-[chuckles]

246
00:19:44.308 --> 00:19:48.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In all honesty,
that stink might not be my blanket.

247
00:19:49.897 --> 00:19:51.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sypha snores softly]

248
00:20:10.334 --> 00:20:12.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish you would stop doing that.

249
00:20:12.836 --> 00:20:13.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's sick.

250
00:20:16.423 --> 00:20:19.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The body is sick. It must be purged.

251
00:20:20.344 --> 00:20:21.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It must be focused.

252
00:20:22.804 --> 00:20:24.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is holy work.

253
00:20:26.141 --> 00:20:29.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How did Dracula draft you
into his service, I wonder?

254
00:20:30.520 --> 00:20:33.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I make purity from human corruption.

255
00:20:34.775 --> 00:20:38.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Human corruption is a stain on the world.

256
00:20:39.613 --> 00:20:41.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was a simple choice.

257
00:20:42.449 --> 00:20:44.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, talking about choices.

258
00:20:44.785 --> 00:20:47.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Carmilla is making a lot of sense to me.

259
00:20:49.206 --> 00:20:51.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-In what way?
-There's no plan.

260
00:20:52.668 --> 00:20:55.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dracula doesn't act
on our recommendations.

261
00:20:55.337 --> 00:20:58.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He barely listens to you and Hector.

262
00:20:58.257 --> 00:21:00.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're just thrashing
around the country randomly.

263
00:21:01.593 --> 00:21:06.098 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There is an intent.
We don't need strict battle plans.

264
00:21:06.556 --> 00:21:08.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We simply follow his intent.

265
00:21:09.393 --> 00:21:11.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We didn't need to hit Gresit right away,
you know.

266
00:21:12.604 --> 00:21:16.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And we should have been made aware
that Alucard was under the bloody city.

267
00:21:17.234 --> 00:21:20.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Alucard is nothing. A spoiled child.

268
00:21:20.696 --> 00:21:24.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Alucard knows almost
as much as Dracula himself,

269
00:21:24.157 --> 00:21:25.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and is almost as strong.

270
00:21:26.285 --> 00:21:29.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And, it turns out,
violently opposed to the war

271
00:21:29.246 --> 00:21:33.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because his human mother
wouldn't have wanted it or some shit.

272
00:21:34.209 --> 00:21:38.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm saying, it may be time for the old man
to sit in his study

273
00:21:38.380 --> 00:21:41.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and let the rest of us
take care of this for him.

274
00:21:41.717 --> 00:21:42.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do it right.

275
00:21:42.968 --> 00:21:46.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Set up livestock pens
and pursue the war properly.

276
00:21:46.888 --> 00:21:47.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Without him.

277
00:21:48.890 --> 00:21:50.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You would betray Dracula?

278
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:52.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not betrayal.

279
00:21:53.353 --> 00:21:57.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unless the old man decides
to be difficult about it.

280
00:22:02.696 --> 00:22:03.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see.

281
00:22:05.949 --> 00:22:07.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

282
00:22:11.955 --> 00:22:14.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Isaac grunts]
-[Godbrand groans]

283
00:22:18.253 --> 00:22:19.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Godbrand chokes]

284
00:22:22.758 --> 00:22:23.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Godbrand grunts]

285
00:22:27.387 --> 00:22:29.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Godbrand groans]

286
00:22:29.181 --> 00:22:32.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank you for revealing to me
how the corruption of the world

287
00:22:32.601 --> 00:22:34.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
has made its way into Dracula's court.

288
00:22:35.395 --> 00:22:38.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you for showing me the truth.

289
00:22:39.733 --> 00:22:41.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Godbrand screams]

290
00:22:43.695 --> 00:22:44.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

291
00:22:44.988 --> 00:22:46.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[muffled screaming]

